C. Felder &amp; R. Felder.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7953BF7FC86AFFF9FF3BFE4AB948FB31" blockId="2.[151,1436,479,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FF3BFE4ABAF8FE49" bold="true" box="[151,444,480,504]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Nomenclatural remarks.</emphasis>
The authorship of 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FD3CFE4AB9BAFE49" box="[656,766,480,504]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FD3CFE4AB9BAFE49" box="[656,766,480,504]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was correctly attributed to Staudinger by 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FB7FFE75BED3FE46" author="Hemming" box="[1235,1431,479,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Hemming, F. (1967) The generic names of the butterflies and their type species (Lepidoptera: Rophalocera), Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Entomology) supl. 9, pp 509." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hemming (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FAFFFE75BECBFE46" box="[1363,1423,479,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FF3BFDAEBA60FDAD" author="Eliot" box="[151,292,516,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Eliot, J. N. (1973) The higher classification of the Lycaenidae (Lepidoptera): a tentative arrangement, Bulletin of the British Museum of natural History (Entomology), 28 (6), 373 - 506." type="journal article" year="1973">
Eliot (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FF4CFDAEBA58FDAD" box="[224,284,516,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1973.0">1973</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FECAFDAEB95DFDAD" author="Johnson" box="[358,537,516,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Johnson, K. (1992) Genera and species of the Neotropical &quot; elfin &quot; - like hairstreak butterflies (Lepidoptera, Lycaenidae, Theclinae), Reports of the Museum of Natural History, University of Wisconsin, 22 (I - II), 1 - 279." type="journal article" year="1992">
Johnson (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FE78FDAEB954FDAD" box="[468,528,516,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, whereas several other authors erroneously credited it to Schatz (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FAE0FDAEBB96FD8E" author="Clench" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Clench, H. K. (1971) Two new hairstreaks from Mexico (Lepidoptera: Lycaenidae), Bulletin of the Allyn Museum, 3, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="1971">
Clench 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FF3BFD8DBB96FD8E" box="[151,210,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FF4DFD8DBAC7FD8E" author="Robbins" box="[225,387,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Robbins, R. K. (2004) Checklist of Eumaeini. 98. Lycaenidae Theclinae, Eumaeini. 118 - 137 pp. In: Lamas, G., Checklist of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A. Hesperioidea- Papilionoidea. Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. J. Heppner (Ed.) Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, 439 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Robbins 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FEE4FD8DBAC7FD8E" box="[328,387,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FE3EFD8DB9ECFD8E" author="Robbins" box="[402,680,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Robbins, R. K., Busby, R. (2008) Phylogeny, taxonomy, and sympatry of Timaeta (Lycaenidae: Theclinae: Eumaeini): an Andean montane forest endemic, Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 151, 205 - 234." type="journal article" year="2008">
Robbins &amp; Busby 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FDC7FD8DB9ECFD8E" box="[619,680,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FC98FD8DB8BCFD8E" author="Hemming" box="[820,1016,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Hemming, F. (1967) The generic names of the butterflies and their type species (Lepidoptera: Rophalocera), Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Entomology) supl. 9, pp 509." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hemming (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FC1AFD8DB8B4FD8E" box="[950,1008,551,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
overlooked the fact that the earliest publication of 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FE90FDE6BAEEFDD5" box="[316,426,588,612]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FE90FDE6BAEEFDD5" box="[316,426,588,612]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an available name appeared on plate 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FCDBFDE6B8D7FDD5" box="[887,915,588,612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="97.0">97</number>
of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FC17FDE6B8B1FDD5" box="[955,1013,588,612]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
I of Staudinger &amp; Schatz's 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FA83FDE6BA7BFD39" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Exotische Schmetterlinge</emphasis>
(
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FEE1FDC5BA94FD36" box="[333,464,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1886.0" valueMax="1888.0" valueMin="1884.0">
<date id="0D5299BFC86AFFF9FEE1FDC5BA94FD36" box="[333,464,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1884" valueMax="1888">1884–1888</date>
</number>
), which was published in late 
<date id="0D5299BFC86AFFF9FC8DFDC5B8DAFD36" box="[801,926,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1888-04">
April 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FCCFFDC5B8DAFD36" box="[867,926,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1888.0">1888</number>
</date>
, and not on pages 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FBC7FDC5BF89FD36" box="[1131,1229,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="288.5" valueMax="289.0" valueMin="288.0">288–289</number>
of the same work, which were published several months later, in early 
<date id="0D5299BFC86AFFF9FD4AFD3EB8D8FD1D" box="[742,924,660,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1888-11">
November 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FCC8FD3EB8D8FD1D" box="[868,924,660,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1888.0">1888</number>
</date>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FC00FD3EBF39FD1D" author="Lamas" box="[940,1149,660,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Lamas, G., Robbins, R. G. &amp; Field W. D. (1995) Bibliography of butterflies. An annotated bibliography of the Neotropical butterflies and skippers (Lepidoptera: Papilionoidea and Hesperioidea). In: Heppner, J. B. (Ed.), Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Gainesville, Association for Tropical Lepidoptera. 124: xiv + 463 pp." type="book" year="1995">
Lamas 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FBACFD3FBF7DFD1D" box="[1024,1081,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FBEDFD3EBF39FD1D" box="[1089,1149,660,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The publication of both the text and plates of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FE24FD12BA86FD61" box="[392,450,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
I of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FE54FD12B851FD61" box="[504,789,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Exotische Schmetterlinge</emphasis>
was clearly the sole responsibility of Staudinger, and any new names appearing in them ought to be attributed to Staudinger alone. Close examination of the text of both 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FF3BFCAABB95FCA9" box="[151,209,768,792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
I and II of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FEFDFCAAB929FCA9" box="[337,621,768,792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Exotische Schmetterlinge</emphasis>
reveals that Schatz was responsible only for 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FBC5FCAABFE7FCA9" box="[1129,1187,768,792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
II, which started publication in 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FEBCFC8EBA0CFC8D" box="[272,328,804,828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1885.0">1885</number>
and was completed in 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FDE0FC8EB9C0FC8D" box="[588,644,804,828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1892.0">1892</number>
by Röber, after Schatz died in 
<date id="0D5299BFC86AFFF9FC48FC8FBF1EFC8D" box="[996,1114,804,829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1887-05">
May 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FBB3FC8EBF1EFC8D" box="[1055,1114,804,828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1887.0">1887</number>
</date>
. Staudinger utilized Schatz's manuscript name 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FECFFCE2BA95FCD1" box="[355,465,840,864]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FECFFCE2BA95FCD1" box="[355,465,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time in plate 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FCAFFCEDB85BFCEE" box="[771,799,839,863]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="97.0">97</number>
of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FCE6FCE2B8C0FCD1" box="[842,900,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
I, and by doing so he unwillingly became the author of the new generic name, as established by Article 50.1 of the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FF7DFC25BA1CFC16" author="ICZN" box="[209,344,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="ICZN (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for zoological Nomenclature, London, 335 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode id="1FFD27BAC86AFFF9FF7DFC25BA50FC16" box="[209,276,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">ICZN</collectionCode>
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FEB0FC25BA1CFC16" box="[284,344,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). A full description of 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FDF4FC3AB982FC19" box="[600,710,912,936]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FDF4FC3AB982FC19" box="[600,710,912,936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared only much later (in 
<date id="0D5299BFC86AFFF9FBB5FC25BFE6FC16" box="[1049,1186,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1892-03">
March 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FBC5FC25BFE6FC16" box="[1129,1186,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1892.0">1892</number>
</date>
) on page 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FABEFC25BE78FC16" box="[1298,1340,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="265.0">265</number>
of 
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FACEFC3ABED8FC19" box="[1378,1436,912,936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Theil</emphasis>
II, under the editorship of Röber. In addition, because Staudinger originally included two species (
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FB5EFC1EB940FC41" authority="C. Felder &amp; R. Felder" authorityName="C. Felder &amp; R. Felder" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Pseudolycaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FB5EFC1EBA4EFC41" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Pseudolycaena platyptera</emphasis>
C. Felder &amp; R. Felder
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FD92FC72B833FC41" authority="Staudinger" authorityName="Staudinger" box="[574,887,984,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapho">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FD92FC72B9B2FC41" box="[574,758,984,1008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra sapho</emphasis>
Staudinger
</taxonomicName>
) in his newly established genus 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FB73FC72BE09FC41" box="[1247,1357,984,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FB73FC72BE09FC41" box="[1247,1357,984,1008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than the single species 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FE0CFC56B957FBA5" box="[416,531,1020,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Pseudolycaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FE0CFC56B957FBA5" box="[416,531,1020,1044]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as erroneously assumed by 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FCFBFC56BF59FBA5" author="Hemming" box="[855,1053,1020,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Hemming, F. (1967) The generic names of the butterflies and their type species (Lepidoptera: Rophalocera), Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Entomology) supl. 9, pp 509." type="journal article" year="1967">
Hemming (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FC75FC56BF51FBA5" box="[985,1045,1020,1044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1967.0">1967</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the generic name lacks a validly designated 
<typeStatus id="A65701DDC86AFFF9FEB9FB8BBA01FB88" box="[277,325,1057,1081]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
species. In order to remedy this situation, and following the kind advice of Prof G. Lamas, I hereby select 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FF4DFBEEB878FBED" authority="C. Felder R. Felder, 1865" authorityName="C. Felder R. Felder" authorityYear="1865" box="[225,828,1092,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Pseudolycaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FF4DFBEEB94CFBED" box="[225,520,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Pseudolycaena platyptera</emphasis>
C. Felder R. Felder, 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FCA8FBEEB878FBED" box="[772,828,1092,1116]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1865.0">1865</number>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="A65701DDC86AFFF9FC38FBEFB880FBEC" box="[916,964,1093,1117]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FBE0FBEEBE04FBED" authority="Staudinger" authorityName="Staudinger" box="[1100,1344,1092,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FBE0FBEEBFFFFBED" box="[1100,1211,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
Staudinger
</taxonomicName>
, [April] 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FF3BFBC2BB96FB31" box="[151,210,1128,1152]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1888.0">1888</number>
, by subsequent designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31F6ECF4C86AFFF9FF6BFB26B904FB5D" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="7953BF7FC86AFFF9FF6BFB26B904FB5D" blockId="2.[151,1436,479,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FF6BFB26BA71FB15" box="[199,309,1164,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FF6BFB26BA71FB15" box="[199,309,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FE71FB26B90CFB15" box="[477,584,1164,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Eumaeini">Eumaeini</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the presence of ten forewing veins, male genitalia lacking a juxta, and male foretarsus fused and stubby tipped (
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FD4CFB1AB818FB79" author="Eliot" box="[736,860,1200,1224]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Eliot, J. N. (1973) The higher classification of the Lycaenidae (Lepidoptera): a tentative arrangement, Bulletin of the British Museum of natural History (Entomology), 28 (6), 373 - 506." type="journal article" year="1973">
Eliot 
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FC8CFB1AB818FB79" box="[800,860,1200,1224]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus was placed within the “ 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FB54FB1ABE23FB79" box="[1272,1383,1200,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4B98636DC86AFFF9FB54FB1ABE23FB79" box="[1272,1383,1200,1224]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
section” of 
<taxonomicName id="BEECC4FCC86AFFF9FF58FB7EBA1BFB5D" box="[244,351,1236,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Eumaeini">Eumaeini</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1D7DC28EC86AFFF9FE25FB7EB978FB5D" author="Robbins" box="[393,572,1236,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" refString="Robbins, R. K. (2004) Checklist of Eumaeini. 98. Lycaenidae Theclinae, Eumaeini. 118 - 137 pp. In: Lamas, G., Checklist of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A. Hesperioidea- Papilionoidea. Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. J. Heppner (Ed.) Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, 439 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">
Robbins (
<number id="CF24AD58C86AFFF9FE5AFB7EB970FB5D" box="[502,564,1236,1260]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
